channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: William A. Anders, Who Flew on First Manned Orbit of the Moon, Dies at 90
item.description: During the 1968 Apollo 8 mission, his color photograph of an emerging Earth, known as “Earthrise,” became an icon and driving force for the environmental movement.

item.title: Where Modi’s B.J.P. Lost Support In India's Election
item.description: Maps show how Modi lost support throughout the country, including in areas that had embraced his party’s Hindu-nationalist ideology.

item.title: Nvidia hits $3 trillion, making CEO Jensen Huang richer than Michael Dell
item.description: Huang, 61, is leading a new wave of tech billionaires

item.title: Macron Hosts Biden in Paris, Honoring a Not Always Easy Bond
item.description: The friendship between France and the U.S. endures. But tensions have mounted over the wars in Gaza and Ukraine, and how Europe can step out of America’s shadow.

item.title: Nicotine patches, like Zyn, are used by 400,000 teens. Here's why some experts say 'it's reasonable to be concerned'
item.description: Health risks of nicotine include a moderately elevated risk of increased blood pressure, heart rate, and a narrowing of the arteries.

item.title: Jordan Bardella, the New Face of France’s Right
item.description: Charismatic and clean cut, shorn of the Le Pen name, the young National Rally leader seems poised to take his party to its best showing ever in European elections on Sunday.

item.title: Tides turn for seafood—more fish were farm-raised than caught in the wild for the first time ever
item.description: Some 90% of aquatic animals that are farmed or fished go to human consumption, per the UN.

item.title: ‘The Bachelor,’ but Make It Belgian Politics
item.description: A reality show called “The Conclave” put Belgium’s political rivals together in a medieval château for a weekend. Can they put aside their differences and help keep the country from coming apart?

item.title: Kia recalls 463,000 Telluride SUVs that could catch fire and cautions drivers to park outdoors
item.description: People may notice a burning or melting smell, or see smoke rising from underneath the seat.

item.title: George Clooney Complained to White House About Biden’s Criticism of I.C.C.
item.description: The actor contacted a top official to protest the president’s denunciation of the move to seek arrest warrants for top Israeli officials over the war in Gaza, a case his wife worked on.

item.title: Canadian Auto Parts Billionaire Faces Sexual Assault Charges
item.description: A police force outside Toronto said that charges against Frank Stronach, 91, relate to episodes from as long ago as the 1980s and as recent as last year.

item.title: Cold Stone Creamery is facing a legal battle after a New York woman discovered that her 'pistachio' ice cream contained no real pistachios
item.description: Rather than the nuts, the dessert contained a mix of water, ethanol, and food coloring.
